9
00:00:43.720 --> 00:00:46.620
(Episode 3)

10
00:00:48.260 --> 00:00:49.520
{\an8}Turning on the water now.

11
00:00:49.890 --> 00:00:52.490
{\an8}Hold on! But wait.

12
00:00:52.930 --> 00:00:55.360
{\an8}How come it doesn't feel like
we're cleaning this together?

13
00:00:56.360 --> 00:00:58.770
{\an8}That's because you're so selfish.

14
00:00:59.130 --> 00:01:01.300
{\an8}- Selfish?
- Yes.

15
00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:05.310
{\an8}- Me? But where are you?
- I'm in your heart. you rascal.

16
00:01:06.980 --> 00:01:08.940
{\an8}Do you have any idea how
much finesse this requires?

17
00:01:09.580 --> 00:01:10.610
{\an8}Chief Park!

18
00:01:11.310 --> 00:01:12.950
{\an8}Did you sell that old call van?

19
00:01:13.250 --> 00:01:17.250
{\an8}- No. we haven't sold it yet.
- Why not? Is it still being fixed?

20
00:01:17.450 --> 00:01:19.050
{\an8}The repairs were finished ages ago.

21
00:01:19.520 --> 00:01:21.489
{\an8}But when it came time
to sell it... I don't know.

22
00:01:21.490 --> 00:01:23.460
{\an8}It's hard to let go.

23
00:01:23.590 --> 00:01:26.360
{\an8}- I know. right?
- So you're just going to keep it?

24
00:01:27.260 --> 00:01:29.400
- No. we have to sell it.
- You should.

25
00:01:29.930 --> 00:01:31.200
I told you to sell it ages ago.

26
00:01:31.730 --> 00:01:32.900
Driver Kim Do Gi. hold on a sec.

27
00:01:33.640 --> 00:01:36.640
Sell it by the end of this week. Or
you have to renew the insurance.

28
00:01:36.810 --> 00:01:37.810
Got it?

29
00:01:38.410 --> 00:01:40.540
She's right. Let's
sell it while we're at it.

30
00:01:40.780 --> 00:01:44.580
- Okay. I'm listing it right now.
- Are you coming or leaving?

31
00:01:44.980 --> 00:01:47.820
- I can give you a ride either way.
- Sweet!

32
00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:53.720
(Sell My Car)

33
00:01:53.790 --> 00:01:54.790
(List Vehicle)

34
00:01:54.860 --> 00:01:56.190
(Listing Complete)

35
00:01:56.260 --> 00:01:58.760
There. It's listed. Okay.
turning on the water now.

36
00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:03.500
Gosh! That feels great!

37
00:02:15.710 --> 00:02:18.050
The Russian Embassy.
Seosomun-dong. Jung-gu.

38
00:02:18.310 --> 00:02:19.510
I think that's in Jeong-dong.

39
00:02:21.480 --> 00:02:22.780
You're right. It is Jeong-dong.

40
00:02:23.350 --> 00:02:26.790
Seosomun-dong. Jeong-dong. Seosomun-ro.

41
00:02:27.690 --> 00:02:28.720
It's all so confusing.

42
00:02:28.860 --> 00:02:32.890
Seosomun-dong has Seosomun-ro.
Sejong-daero. and Deoksugung-gil.

43
00:02:33.160 --> 00:02:34.700
In Seosomun-dong.

44
00:02:35.060 --> 00:02:37.700
it's Seo. Se. Deok.

45
00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:39.800
Seo... Seo-Se-Deok.

46
00:02:41.040 --> 00:02:42.040
Next.

47
00:02:42.670 --> 00:02:45.969
Lend license. cancelled.
Return to transport operator.

48
00:02:45.970 --> 00:02:47.410
The transferee is responsible.

49
00:02:47.540 --> 00:02:51.250
Ren-Can... Ret-Op... Trans-Buy.
Ren-Can-Ret-Op. Trans-Buy.

50
00:02:52.510 --> 00:02:53.520
If I can just memorize this...

51
00:02:53.580 --> 00:02:55.550
(Driver Aptitude Test Center)

52
00:02:55.620 --> 00:02:57.720
(Certification Exam Site)

53
00:03:00.090 --> 00:03:01.190
Thanks for the ride.

54
00:03:10.430 --> 00:03:14.240
Seo... Seo-Se-Deok.
Ren-Can-Ret-Op. Trans-Buy.

55
00:03:14.300 --> 00:03:16.340
(No photography)

56
00:03:23.510 --> 00:03:26.010
(2025 Taxi Driver
Qualification Exam Results)

57
00:03:29.820 --> 00:03:32.090
(Certification Exam Site)

58
00:03:38.530 --> 00:03:39.630
Driver Kim Do Gi.

59
00:03:40.130 --> 00:03:41.300
You're still here?

60
00:03:42.430 --> 00:03:45.000
Yes. I was waiting to congratulate you.

61
00:03:46.870 --> 00:03:49.800
How can you say that when I look like this?

62
00:03:50.670 --> 00:03:53.410
But you look absolutely ecstatic to me.

63
00:03:54.040 --> 00:03:56.480
Ecstatic? Please.

64
00:03:57.250 --> 00:03:58.880
It was a piece of cake.

65
00:04:01.120 --> 00:04:03.550
(Taxi Driver's License)

66
00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:06.390
If I'd gotten one more
right. I would've scored a 90.

67
00:04:06.590 --> 00:04:10.630
I got confused if the German
Embassy was in Jung-gu or Jongno-gu.

68
00:04:12.790 --> 00:04:13.800
Here.

69
00:04:14.800 --> 00:04:15.860
Here's a little something for passing.

70
00:04:16.600 --> 00:04:20.970
- What is it?
- A taxi for your new license.

71
00:04:23.070 --> 00:04:24.070
A tax...

72
00:04:24.940 --> 00:04:27.280
When did you even get this?

73
00:04:28.080 --> 00:04:30.010
You didn't even know I
was taking the test today.

74
00:04:30.310 --> 00:04:33.110
If you had failed. I
would've just played dumb.

75
00:04:38.150 --> 00:04:39.320
This is so cute.

76
00:04:40.390 --> 00:04:41.420
Thank you.

77
00:04:45.490 --> 00:04:46.590
Then...

78
00:04:50.830 --> 00:04:52.500
I'll drive. Hop in.

79
00:04:59.910 --> 00:05:03.810
You're An Go Eun's first
customer. Where to. sir?

80
00:05:04.810 --> 00:05:07.450
- I'm not sure.
- Is there anywhere you want to go?

81
00:05:08.420 --> 00:05:09.950
How far can you take me?

82
00:05:11.850 --> 00:05:14.190
Until we run out of gas?

83
00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:20.760
Perfect.

84
00:05:21.600 --> 00:05:26.300
(Taxi Driver 3)

85
00:05:26.430 --> 00:05:28.500
(Rainbow Taxi)

86
00:05:40.150 --> 00:05:42.050
Last week near Gangnam Station.

87
00:05:42.120 --> 00:05:44.890
a Rolls-Royce drove on the sidewalk.

88
00:05:45.120 --> 00:05:49.620
A woman in her 30s was
struck. breaking both of her legs...

89
00:06:08.880 --> 00:06:09.910
Driver Oh?

90
00:06:20.860 --> 00:06:23.360
Here. have some tea.

91
00:06:28.360 --> 00:06:32.030
How do you like it? Going
private after all those years.

92
00:06:32.800 --> 00:06:34.470
A taxi's a taxi.

93
00:06:35.440 --> 00:06:36.900
Let's see.

94
00:06:37.710 --> 00:06:40.540
Is Ji Eun graduating
from college this year?

95
00:06:40.640 --> 00:06:44.750
Yes. She's so busy studying
for the civil service exam.

96
00:06:49.920 --> 00:06:51.020
Actually...

97
00:06:58.860 --> 00:07:00.260
It's all right. you can tell me.

98
00:07:02.960 --> 00:07:04.070
It's just that...

99
00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:09.770
Could I borrow some
money? Around 3.000 dollars.

100
00:07:10.240 --> 00:07:13.470
But it might take me a
while to pay you back.

101
00:07:17.280 --> 00:07:20.950
Don't worry. I'm in no rush. Just
pay me back when you're able.

102
00:07:22.080 --> 00:07:23.350
Thanks. Mr. Jang.

103
00:07:23.580 --> 00:07:26.190
I can send it to the same account
you used for your salary. right?

104
00:07:26.250 --> 00:07:29.720
Would it be possible to get it
in cash instead of a transfer?

105
00:07:31.260 --> 00:07:33.130
- Cash?
- Goodness.

106
00:07:33.700 --> 00:07:37.070
I feel so ashamed. showing up
after all this time to ask for this.

107
00:07:37.200 --> 00:07:39.070
No. not at all. Please. don't say that.

108
00:07:39.570 --> 00:07:42.770
I'll go to the bank tomorrow morning
and have the cash ready for you.

109
00:07:44.310 --> 00:07:47.280
I've taken up enough of
your time. I'll be on my way.

110
00:07:47.340 --> 00:07:49.180
Wait. you should at least stay for dinner.

111
00:07:49.210 --> 00:07:50.779
I have another appointment. I'll get going.

112
00:07:50.780 --> 00:07:52.150
- Don't come out.
- But...

113
00:07:53.850 --> 00:07:57.490
Yes. I can be there in 10
minutes. And the fee is 30 dollars.

114
00:07:57.750 --> 00:08:00.220
And you're in the parking
garage. on level B3. right?

115
00:08:00.390 --> 00:08:03.090
Yes. I'm heading out
now. so I'll be there shortly.

116
00:08:03.190 --> 00:08:05.530
Okay. I'll be right there. Yes. thank you.

117
00:08:25.710 --> 00:08:28.020
There's a bit of a scratch
here on the front bumper.

118
00:08:28.420 --> 00:08:32.350
- Gosh. talk about eagle eyes.
- Even I can see that.

119
00:08:32.850 --> 00:08:35.690
But "scratch" is such a harsh
word for that little blemish.

120
00:08:35.760 --> 00:08:38.460
I'd call it a beauty mark. Just a tiny one.

121
00:08:38.860 --> 00:08:39.990
Right.

122
00:08:43.160 --> 00:08:44.830
There are a lot of screw holes.

123
00:08:45.600 --> 00:08:46.770
Looks like it's been modified.

124
00:08:46.900 --> 00:08:49.300
Yes. It's because we had to install
a lot of communications gear...

125
00:08:49.370 --> 00:08:51.510
That just means she's a jack-of-all-trades.

126
00:08:56.080 --> 00:08:58.680
The paint job is in
relatively good condition.

127
00:08:59.210 --> 00:09:00.450
It's practically brand new.

128
00:09:00.520 --> 00:09:04.320
Right. It was in a huge
accident. so we just...

129
00:09:05.890 --> 00:09:09.390
Because he's such a
careful and delicate driver.

130
00:09:10.390 --> 00:09:12.330
I see a few accidents
on its record. though.

131
00:09:13.800 --> 00:09:16.500
Yes. but they were nothing.
Just minor fender-benders.

132
00:09:18.470 --> 00:09:21.370
I can't even remember now.
Was it just a little scrape?

133
00:09:21.440 --> 00:09:23.770
What are you talking about?
The repair bills were thousands...

134
00:09:26.640 --> 00:09:30.410
He's a very careful driver.
A really meticulous guy.

135
00:09:32.080 --> 00:09:34.720
Hey. we can't lie about this.

136
00:09:34.820 --> 00:09:37.020
We have to think about
this car's next owner.

137
00:09:37.390 --> 00:09:38.420
You little...

138
00:09:38.790 --> 00:09:40.760
You're not wrong. so I
can't even argue with you.

139
00:09:41.660 --> 00:09:43.930
Here's something even you can't deny.

140
00:09:44.890 --> 00:09:48.000
Sir. buying this car means...

141
00:09:48.730 --> 00:09:50.870
you're not just buying a car.
you're buying our memories.

142
00:09:51.300 --> 00:09:54.770
He's right about that. It
holds many special memories.

143
00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:57.000
All right. I get it.

144
00:09:58.710 --> 00:09:59.970
Memories. That's nice.

145
00:10:00.370 --> 00:10:04.410
We'll add 1.000 for the "memories"
and buy it for a total of 11.000.

146
00:10:08.880 --> 00:10:11.220
I'm just going to take it for a quick spin.

147
00:10:11.290 --> 00:10:13.450
- Of course. Take your time.
- Take your time.

148
00:10:23.430 --> 00:10:25.970
Actually seeing it go
makes me feel kind of weird.

149
00:10:26.330 --> 00:10:28.640
Tell me about it. I guess
we really got attached.

150
00:10:44.750 --> 00:10:46.520
What's taking him so long?

151
00:10:48.260 --> 00:10:49.290
I know.

152
00:10:50.060 --> 00:10:51.590
He's been gone way too long.

153
00:10:56.230 --> 00:10:57.900
Manager Go Deok Su.

154
00:10:58.270 --> 00:11:02.440
When he said "a quick spin."
did he mean all of Seoul?

155
00:11:02.670 --> 00:11:03.670
Let's give him a call.

156
00:11:04.810 --> 00:11:07.140
I already told you. His phone is off.

157
00:11:08.780 --> 00:11:11.910
So what. we just have to keep waiting?

158
00:11:12.210 --> 00:11:13.210
He'll be back.

159
00:11:13.650 --> 00:11:15.580
He's probably just
driving and can't pick up.

160
00:11:17.050 --> 00:11:18.390
Let's just wait a little longer.

161
00:11:19.790 --> 00:11:20.820
All right.

162
00:11:26.260 --> 00:11:27.260
What?

163
00:11:33.830 --> 00:11:36.070
(Taxi Driver's License)

164
00:11:36.170 --> 00:11:38.640
(Company: Rainbow Taxi. Name: An Go Eun)

165
00:11:48.150 --> 00:11:49.620
You scared me.

166
00:11:49.650 --> 00:11:52.920
- You could've made a noise.
- Come on. now.

167
00:11:53.650 --> 00:11:55.790
Go Eun. please. you have to help us out.

168
00:11:56.190 --> 00:11:59.960
We waited there all night for
him. but he never showed up!

169
00:12:00.090 --> 00:12:02.230
It was his plan all along.

170
00:12:03.060 --> 00:12:04.430
Then just give him a call.

171
00:12:04.500 --> 00:12:07.800
We already did! Gyeong
Gu and I kept calling him.

172
00:12:07.870 --> 00:12:11.240
- We can't get a hold of him at all.
- This is a total scam.

173
00:12:11.540 --> 00:12:15.640
- You have to catch that guy.
- So. like I said. call the police.

174
00:12:15.740 --> 00:12:19.410
The police are far away. but
you're here with us. Go Eun.

175
00:12:19.480 --> 00:12:22.350
I have way too much to do. so
I'm about to make myself scarce.

176
00:12:23.550 --> 00:12:24.720
Stay back.

177
00:12:24.790 --> 00:12:26.820
You were the one who told
us to sell it quickly. so we did!

178
00:12:27.660 --> 00:12:29.490
So. are you saying this is my fault?

179
00:12:29.560 --> 00:12:32.230
Hey. what's with all the
noise? What's going on here?

180
00:12:32.290 --> 00:12:35.700
They sold it to some con artist.
and now they want me to find it.

181
00:12:35.760 --> 00:12:36.900
A con artist?

182
00:12:37.130 --> 00:12:40.130
We waited for him all night
and only left because of the rain.

183
00:12:40.200 --> 00:12:43.240
This guy. a "used car
dealer." said he'd test drive it...

184
00:12:43.300 --> 00:12:44.340
Hang on a second.

185
00:12:46.410 --> 00:12:49.080
Yes. Driver Oh. I've
been waiting for your call.

186
00:12:49.210 --> 00:12:52.379
- I won't need to borrow that money.
- What?

187
00:12:52.380 --> 00:12:54.280
Sorry to have worried you for nothing.

188
00:12:54.650 --> 00:12:57.250
- You're busy. so I'll let you go.
- Wait. Driver Oh.

189
00:13:05.360 --> 00:13:07.090
Go Eun. you know Driver Oh. right?

190
00:13:07.130 --> 00:13:10.360
Look up Driver Oh's home
address and text it to me right away.

191
00:13:10.460 --> 00:13:11.630
- Yes. sir.
- But...

192
00:13:12.230 --> 00:13:14.140
- Go Eun...
- Gosh. just go dry yourselves off.

193
00:13:14.440 --> 00:13:15.440
But...

194
00:13:18.270 --> 00:13:20.440
Hey. looks like Mr. Jang
is leaving. What do we do?

195
00:13:21.640 --> 00:13:22.710
Should we wait?

196
00:13:22.880 --> 00:13:26.310
- He said to hang on. so let's wait.
- Okay.

197
00:13:40.060 --> 00:13:42.160
- Ji Eun. you're home.
- Hello. sir.

198
00:13:42.230 --> 00:13:43.230
Is your mom home?

199
00:13:43.300 --> 00:13:46.330
My mom's not feeling well. She
took medicine and is sleeping.

200
00:13:47.330 --> 00:13:48.770
- Please. come in.
- Thanks.

201
00:13:52.970 --> 00:13:55.840
So your dad had an accident
working as a designated driver?

202
00:13:58.010 --> 00:13:59.550
He broke his wrist.

203
00:14:00.110 --> 00:14:02.320
so he had surgery and
is in the hospital now.

204
00:14:02.580 --> 00:14:05.850
But I thought he was doing
well with his private taxi.

205
00:14:05.990 --> 00:14:09.620
I didn't know Dad was a
designated driver until the accident.

206
00:14:10.930 --> 00:14:12.090
Oh. dear.

207
00:14:13.960 --> 00:14:14.960
And...

208
00:14:18.070 --> 00:14:19.930
I found this in his drawer.

209
00:14:21.700 --> 00:14:24.740
Hey. these are divorce papers.

210
00:14:25.710 --> 00:14:28.410
I have no idea what's
going through his head.

211
00:14:29.340 --> 00:14:30.910
He won't answer me when I ask.

212
00:14:32.250 --> 00:14:33.710
Which hospital is your dad in right now?

213
00:14:43.620 --> 00:14:44.690
Driver Oh.

214
00:14:52.470 --> 00:14:54.400
(Onjoongang Hospital)

215
00:15:19.290 --> 00:15:20.430
Driver Oh!

216
00:15:22.360 --> 00:15:23.360
Driver Oh!

217
00:15:23.930 --> 00:15:25.330
Driver Oh. wait!

218
00:15:28.040 --> 00:15:29.040
Driver Oh.

219
00:15:29.940 --> 00:15:33.270
I don't know what's going
on. but please. just talk to me.

220
00:15:34.280 --> 00:15:35.780
There's no other way.

221
00:15:38.080 --> 00:15:39.710
I have to die right here.

222
00:15:40.180 --> 00:15:42.680
- It'll all be over.
- What do you mean. be over?

223
00:15:45.090 --> 00:15:46.390
What about the people you'll leave behind?

224
00:15:47.120 --> 00:15:49.360
The pain you're going through right now!

225
00:15:50.090 --> 00:15:53.590
The people left behind will
carry that pain. only magnified.

226
00:15:55.530 --> 00:15:57.570
They'll have to carry that
weight for the rest of their lives.

227
00:15:57.830 --> 00:15:59.000
Are you okay with that?

228
00:16:01.740 --> 00:16:02.740
Just come here.

229
00:16:03.400 --> 00:16:04.440
I'll help you.

230
00:16:05.440 --> 00:16:06.440
Okay?

231
00:16:07.010 --> 00:16:10.710
There's nothing more I can do.

232
00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:12.550
That's not true!

233
00:16:13.850 --> 00:16:16.380
There are always other options.

234
00:16:17.420 --> 00:16:20.420
There is so much you
can still do. All right?

235
00:16:22.060 --> 00:16:23.060
I...

236
00:16:24.330 --> 00:16:26.690
Those jerks got me.

237
00:16:27.900 --> 00:16:30.560
and there's no way out.

238
00:16:33.600 --> 00:16:34.740
Please...

239
00:16:38.910 --> 00:16:40.340
Please just take my hand.

240
00:16:42.080 --> 00:16:43.240
Hey. Come on.

241
00:17:08.570 --> 00:17:10.770
It's all right. You're okay.

242
00:17:11.510 --> 00:17:12.510
You're okay.

243
00:17:17.910 --> 00:17:19.280
Whatever happened.

244
00:17:20.310 --> 00:17:21.850
you can tell me everything.

245
00:17:22.880 --> 00:17:23.880
Everything.

246
00:17:31.360 --> 00:17:32.360
(Driver Test Evaluation Report)

247
00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:34.560
Looks like all your paperwork is in order.

248
00:17:35.530 --> 00:17:36.530
But...

249
00:17:37.230 --> 00:17:39.130
What is it? Are you not
happy with the price?

250
00:17:39.330 --> 00:17:42.270
No. it's just much lower than I expected.

251
00:17:51.410 --> 00:17:52.850
So a low price is a problem now?

252
00:17:54.480 --> 00:17:57.120
I'm sorry if it came off that way.

253
00:17:59.590 --> 00:18:02.220
Right now. the going rate
for a Seoul taxi number...

254
00:18:02.690 --> 00:18:05.830
is trading at about 120.000
dollars. give or take 5.000.

255
00:18:06.730 --> 00:18:10.030
This particular license is for sale
due to the owner's poor health.

256
00:18:10.200 --> 00:18:11.970
So it came to us as a distress sale.

257
00:18:12.370 --> 00:18:15.140
So we listed it at a 25-percent
discount off the market rate.

258
00:18:15.200 --> 00:18:17.140
and you were the very first person to call.

259
00:18:17.910 --> 00:18:21.910
I was scrolling through listings.
and yours suddenly popped up.

260
00:18:22.080 --> 00:18:23.880
So I knew I had to jump on it right away.

261
00:18:23.940 --> 00:18:25.410
Look. I have another appointment to get to.

262
00:18:25.810 --> 00:18:27.750
so I'll just assume you're
withdrawing your offer.

263
00:18:27.820 --> 00:18:29.680
and I'll contact the next person
on the waiting list right away.

264
00:18:29.780 --> 00:18:31.420
Goodness. withdraw?

265
00:18:32.090 --> 00:18:33.090
Of course not.

266
00:18:33.450 --> 00:18:35.890
The owner wants to have cash
in hand by the end of the day.

267
00:18:35.960 --> 00:18:38.130
If we waste time. we both lose. don't we?

268
00:18:38.790 --> 00:18:39.830
Right. I understand.

269
00:18:40.630 --> 00:18:43.060
I'll take the deal.

270
00:18:46.970 --> 00:18:48.139
- Manager Yang.
- Yes. sir.

271
00:18:48.140 --> 00:18:49.169
His papers check out.

272
00:18:49.170 --> 00:18:50.570
- so process with the contract.
- Yes. sir.

273
00:18:51.610 --> 00:18:53.740
- Assistant Manager Yoo. you there?
- Yes. sir.

274
00:18:53.840 --> 00:18:56.680
Pull the taxi out front so
it's easy for him to leave.

275
00:18:56.980 --> 00:18:58.110
Right away. sir.

276
00:19:01.520 --> 00:19:04.050
I'm sorry to rush off. My
next appointment is tight.

277
00:19:04.220 --> 00:19:07.150
Not at all. I'm the one who held you up.

278
00:19:07.290 --> 00:19:08.290
My apologies.

279
00:19:12.130 --> 00:19:13.130
Oh. right.

280
00:19:13.590 --> 00:19:16.130
- Make a separate cashback contract.
- Right.

281
00:19:16.360 --> 00:19:19.630
My manager here will explain
it all. Just listen to him and sign.

282
00:19:20.300 --> 00:19:22.070
- All right. then.
- Okay.

283
00:19:23.300 --> 00:19:24.300
Take care. sir.

284
00:19:28.210 --> 00:19:29.340
Hello. there. It's a pleasure.

285
00:19:29.910 --> 00:19:32.150
I'll be assisting you
with the contract process.

286
00:19:32.480 --> 00:19:36.120
That was Cha Byeong Jin. the owner. right?

287
00:19:36.280 --> 00:19:38.250
Yes. that's our boss.

288
00:19:38.720 --> 00:19:40.020
And is that for real?

289
00:19:40.620 --> 00:19:43.290
Absolutely. Our boss.

290
00:19:43.660 --> 00:19:46.260
is indeed a lawyer who passed the Bar Exam.

291
00:19:46.630 --> 00:19:49.260
- Is that right?
- He's so passionate about cars...

292
00:19:49.900 --> 00:19:52.470
that he decided to run
this dealership himself.

293
00:19:52.870 --> 00:19:54.940
A total gearhead.

294
00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:56.840
Hearing that he's a lawyer...

295
00:19:57.270 --> 00:19:59.940
- inspires trust.
- All right. have a seat.

296
00:20:00.440 --> 00:20:04.550
All right. let me explain
the cashback contract.

297
00:20:05.180 --> 00:20:06.210
Cashback?

298
00:20:07.250 --> 00:20:10.020
If we report the sale at a price
that's well below the market rate.

299
00:20:10.080 --> 00:20:13.890
others in our industry would
see it as disrupting the market.

300
00:20:14.090 --> 00:20:18.290
We report the sale at market
rate. and then every month.

301
00:20:18.730 --> 00:20:22.900
- we send cashback to your account.
- I see.

302
00:20:22.960 --> 00:20:25.130
Your private taxi is right out front.

303
00:20:25.730 --> 00:20:26.800
Congratulations.

304
00:20:27.600 --> 00:20:28.600
Congratulations.

305
00:20:29.170 --> 00:20:30.940
Gosh. this is a nice taxi.

306
00:20:31.370 --> 00:20:34.270
We buy used cars. so if you know
any other drivers looking to sell.

307
00:20:34.410 --> 00:20:37.010
- please send them our way.
- Of course.

308
00:20:37.580 --> 00:20:39.780
- Great. thank you.
- No. we're grateful.

309
00:20:39.910 --> 00:20:42.780
All right. let's get this wrapped up.

310
00:20:43.020 --> 00:20:45.020
- Okay.
- Right here. Press down.

311
00:20:50.990 --> 00:20:53.260
(Bar Exam Certificate of
Qualification. Cha Byeong Jin)

312
00:20:53.790 --> 00:20:56.660
- But he is a lawyer.
- Then why is a lawyer selling cars?

313
00:20:57.230 --> 00:20:59.130
He was disbarred.

314
00:20:59.400 --> 00:21:01.340
He killed someone in a
drunk driving hit-and-run.

315
00:21:03.300 --> 00:21:06.270
And he only served six years in prison.

316
00:21:06.710 --> 00:21:09.910
That he still brazenly displays
it even after being disbarred...

317
00:21:10.210 --> 00:21:12.010
shows how proud he must still be.

318
00:21:12.250 --> 00:21:14.850
Wait. I have a question.

319
00:21:15.380 --> 00:21:17.920
Doesn't Driver Oh qualify for
his own private taxi license?

320
00:21:18.250 --> 00:21:20.320
Why would he spend so much
money buying one from someone else?

321
00:21:20.790 --> 00:21:25.290
It's because of the Taxi Cap System.
Private taxi licenses are limited.

322
00:21:25.690 --> 00:21:28.500
So. only when someone
turns in their license...

323
00:21:28.560 --> 00:21:30.600
can a new license be issued.

324
00:21:32.070 --> 00:21:35.070
Instead of waiting forever for
a turn that might never come.

325
00:21:35.440 --> 00:21:39.040
it's become standard practice to
buy a license from a private seller.

326
00:21:40.270 --> 00:21:44.850
After investing so much money
in it. he barely got to use it...

327
00:21:44.910 --> 00:21:47.079
before it was revoked overnight.

328
00:21:47.080 --> 00:21:48.650
- Revoked?
- Why?

329
00:21:53.720 --> 00:21:56.860
Honey. wait. You forgot your lunch.

330
00:21:58.730 --> 00:22:02.960
I made bone broth for your
knees. Don't let it go to waste. okay?

331
00:22:03.030 --> 00:22:05.770
Gosh. I'll have to eat
this right after my first fare.

332
00:22:06.070 --> 00:22:07.070
I'm off.

333
00:22:07.130 --> 00:22:11.340
You'll get hungry again quickly.
Eat it at a proper mealtime. okay?

334
00:22:11.970 --> 00:22:14.240
- Ji Eun. be careful on the road.
- Okay.

335
00:22:15.510 --> 00:22:17.680
I thought you could finally
rest with your own taxi.

336
00:22:18.050 --> 00:22:19.050
but I guess not.

337
00:22:19.110 --> 00:22:23.580
I'll pay your loans by graduation
so you can study without worries.

338
00:22:24.150 --> 00:22:26.890
I hear it takes a long time to
prepare for the civil service exam.

339
00:22:27.020 --> 00:22:30.259
Dad. I'll pass the first
time. so don't worry.

340
00:22:30.260 --> 00:22:31.730
Go on. I'll see you later.

341
00:22:32.760 --> 00:22:34.360
- Dad.
- Yes?

342
00:22:34.960 --> 00:22:35.960
ASD!

343
00:22:36.460 --> 00:22:37.500
What?

344
00:22:38.370 --> 00:22:40.730
Another safe day! I'm off!

345
00:22:43.340 --> 00:22:44.640
Another safe day.

346
00:22:45.710 --> 00:22:46.710
ASD?

347
00:23:01.190 --> 00:23:03.020
Hey! What do you think
you're doing over there?

348
00:23:03.260 --> 00:23:04.760
Are you the owner of this taxi?

349
00:23:04.860 --> 00:23:06.690
Yes. I'm the owner of this private taxi.

350
00:23:06.960 --> 00:23:08.960
So what are you doing with my car?

351
00:23:09.460 --> 00:23:13.200
Under the Passenger Transport Act.
your taxi license has been revoked.

352
00:23:13.370 --> 00:23:15.570
What? What do you mean. revoked?

353
00:23:15.770 --> 00:23:18.670
It says here you have a conviction
for a drunk driving accident.

354
00:23:18.910 --> 00:23:19.910
Me?

355
00:23:20.810 --> 00:23:23.080
There must be some
kind of misunderstanding.

356
00:23:23.410 --> 00:23:24.950
I don't drink at all.

357
00:23:25.180 --> 00:23:26.510
And what's this about a car accident?

358
00:23:26.750 --> 00:23:30.180
We're just following orders.
sir. We don't know the specifics.

359
00:23:30.250 --> 00:23:32.020
We will now proceed to
confiscate the license plate.

360
00:23:33.290 --> 00:23:36.990
Please. don't. I'm telling you
I've never done anything like that!

361
00:23:37.190 --> 00:23:38.360
Don't take it up with us.

362
00:23:38.730 --> 00:23:40.190
Go take it up with the people
who sold you the license.

363
00:23:43.560 --> 00:23:45.730
(Notice of Administrative Disposition)

364
00:23:47.530 --> 00:23:49.070
And just like that. overnight.

365
00:23:49.140 --> 00:23:50.640
(Another Safe Day)

366
00:23:50.700 --> 00:23:54.240
my private taxi license was taken away.

367
00:24:05.790 --> 00:24:07.920
Sir. should I take this ride?

368
00:24:12.960 --> 00:24:14.730
Hey. you. You remember me. right?

369
00:24:15.060 --> 00:24:17.660
You guys knew all along.
and you tricked me. didn't you?

370
00:24:18.600 --> 00:24:19.870
Tricked you?

371
00:24:20.430 --> 00:24:22.700
About what? Sir. can we talk over here?

372
00:24:26.340 --> 00:24:29.640
- What seems to be the problem?
- The old owner had a DUI.

373
00:24:30.040 --> 00:24:33.050
- so they took my license plate.
- Really? Is that what happened?

374
00:24:33.980 --> 00:24:37.950
He just asked us to
sell the license quickly.

375
00:24:38.050 --> 00:24:40.090
so we simply brokered
the deal for a low price.

376
00:24:41.320 --> 00:24:43.890
- You know how it is.
- Stop lying.

377
00:24:45.160 --> 00:24:46.160
You knew all along.

378
00:24:47.990 --> 00:24:50.960
What. you think we're
psychics or something?

379
00:24:51.200 --> 00:24:53.900
I'm going to report you all to the police.

380
00:24:54.130 --> 00:24:56.770
Just wait and see. I'll
report you to the police!

381
00:24:56.900 --> 00:24:58.170
Please.

382
00:25:01.070 --> 00:25:02.140
Go ahead.

383
00:25:04.440 --> 00:25:05.610
Report us to the police.

384
00:25:06.680 --> 00:25:07.680
Okay?

385
00:25:08.820 --> 00:25:09.950
Now stop disrupting our business.

386
00:25:14.590 --> 00:25:15.790
Hi. there.

387
00:25:17.390 --> 00:25:20.290
He comes in sometimes.
spouting all sorts of nonsense.

388
00:25:24.460 --> 00:25:28.670
(Civil Service Center)

389
00:25:28.740 --> 00:25:33.210
I understand your situation.
but our hands are tied.

390
00:25:33.770 --> 00:25:34.840
What do you mean. your hands are tied?

391
00:25:34.940 --> 00:25:38.150
Though your license was transferred.
the law requires its revocation.

392
00:25:40.680 --> 00:25:43.249
But the previous owner
was the one who drank.

393
00:25:43.250 --> 00:25:45.090
All I did was buy the license.

394
00:25:45.520 --> 00:25:49.590
so why is my license being revoked?
What kind of insane law is that?

395
00:25:49.720 --> 00:25:51.730
Yes. I understand you feel this is unfair.

396
00:25:52.060 --> 00:25:53.230
but that's just the way the law is written.

397
00:25:53.890 --> 00:25:54.900
I'm sorry about this.

398
00:25:56.330 --> 00:25:59.570
If all you can say is sorry.
what am I supposed to do?

399
00:25:59.800 --> 00:26:02.440
Who else am I supposed
to talk to about this?

400
00:26:03.800 --> 00:26:05.540
You could try inquiring at
the relevant government office.

401
00:26:07.140 --> 00:26:10.510
But if you drive without a license
plate even if you're in a rush.

402
00:26:11.080 --> 00:26:12.450
you can be fined.

403
00:26:19.990 --> 00:26:24.120
(Vehicle Registration)

404
00:26:25.660 --> 00:26:29.300
Hi. I was told my taxi
license was suddenly revoked.

405
00:26:29.330 --> 00:26:32.130
Our department doesn't handle
that. Please try the seventh floor.

406
00:26:32.330 --> 00:26:35.470
- What? The seventh floor?
- Next.

407
00:26:35.740 --> 00:26:36.870
Okay. thank you.

408
00:26:42.980 --> 00:26:46.180
There's nothing we can do
either. We're just following the law.

409
00:26:46.550 --> 00:26:49.050
If everyone just keeps telling me no.

410
00:26:49.350 --> 00:26:52.590
then who am I supposed to turn to for help?

411
00:26:52.790 --> 00:26:55.790
I'm afraid you'll have to
go to the police station.

412
00:26:55.960 --> 00:26:58.890
I just told you. I just came
from the police station!

413
00:26:59.630 --> 00:27:03.330
If you truly feel this is unjust.
you can file an administrative case.

414
00:27:03.730 --> 00:27:04.730
Sir.

415
00:27:05.500 --> 00:27:07.330
Please don't just tell me it can't be done.

416
00:27:07.800 --> 00:27:09.970
Please just help me this one time. Please?

417
00:27:12.610 --> 00:27:14.710
Have you spoken with the previous owner?

418
00:27:16.540 --> 00:27:18.180
The previous owner?

419
00:27:19.650 --> 00:27:22.250
The previous owner
was arrested for the DUI...

420
00:27:22.820 --> 00:27:24.350
and was in prison.

421
00:27:24.990 --> 00:27:26.450
He said he was broke.

422
00:27:27.190 --> 00:27:28.890
so I couldn't even bring up the money.

423
00:27:31.320 --> 00:27:33.430
- Hello?
- Hey. honey.

424
00:27:33.730 --> 00:27:35.100
Did you get a lot of fares today?

425
00:27:38.000 --> 00:27:40.070
Yes. today...

426
00:27:41.370 --> 00:27:43.970
By the way. how was the bone
broth? You finished it all. right?

427
00:27:44.070 --> 00:27:46.570
Yes. it was delicious.

428
00:27:47.240 --> 00:27:48.710
Of course it was. Who do you think made it?

429
00:27:49.240 --> 00:27:52.910
- Drive safe. I'll see you at home.
- Yes. okay. Talk to you later.

430
00:28:52.340 --> 00:28:53.640
What am I going to do?

431
00:28:55.140 --> 00:28:57.710
How could they all do this to me?

432
00:29:00.580 --> 00:29:01.580
How...

433
00:29:24.140 --> 00:29:26.810
But wait. isn't this a
completely unfair situation?

434
00:29:27.370 --> 00:29:30.240
Why should Driver Oh have to pay
for the previous owner's mistake?

435
00:29:30.580 --> 00:29:34.250
Under current law. if a private
taxi license holder gets a DUI.

436
00:29:34.380 --> 00:29:36.250
their license can be revoked.

437
00:29:36.980 --> 00:29:38.320
Looking at the circumstances.

438
00:29:38.850 --> 00:29:42.720
it seems the broker bought a license
about to be revoked on the cheap...

439
00:29:42.890 --> 00:29:44.690
and then pawned it off on Driver Oh.

440
00:29:44.990 --> 00:29:46.460
That's fraud.

441
00:29:46.730 --> 00:29:50.330
- He can claim he didn't know.
- What?

442
00:29:50.660 --> 00:29:53.630
The taxi's previous owner. the broker.

443
00:29:53.930 --> 00:29:56.040
the public official. the police.

444
00:29:56.970 --> 00:30:00.740
Driver Oh was caught in a
blind spot between all of them.

445
00:30:01.270 --> 00:30:02.610
They knew about the loophole in the law...

446
00:30:03.780 --> 00:30:05.250
and exploited that blind spot.

447
00:30:05.810 --> 00:30:08.720
Still. Driver Oh fought
desperately not to give up.

448
00:30:09.380 --> 00:30:12.320
Then why did he go all
the way up to the rooftop?

449
00:30:14.150 --> 00:30:15.420
Because that wasn't the end of it.

450
00:30:19.960 --> 00:30:21.590
We're here. sir.

451
00:30:35.580 --> 00:30:36.940
Yes. this is your designated driver.

452
00:30:37.480 --> 00:30:41.180
Yes. I'm nearby. It'll take
me about ten minutes.

453
00:30:41.250 --> 00:30:43.050
Okay. I'll be right there. Thank you.

454
00:30:44.550 --> 00:30:46.150
Excuse me. sir. The key...

455
00:30:53.730 --> 00:30:54.730
Thank you.

456
00:30:56.930 --> 00:31:00.700
- Yes. designated driver speaking.
- Yes. this is Noblesse Motors.

457
00:31:01.200 --> 00:31:02.200
What is this regarding?

458
00:31:02.470 --> 00:31:06.070
I'm calling with the repair
estimate for your luxury car.

459
00:31:08.210 --> 00:31:10.280
What are you talking about.
calling me suddenly like this?

460
00:31:10.380 --> 00:31:13.450
The accident was
minor. but it's a luxury car.

461
00:31:13.680 --> 00:31:15.720
so the estimate came out to 40.000 dollars.

462
00:31:16.720 --> 00:31:19.490
A luxury car? What on
earth are you talking about?

463
00:31:19.790 --> 00:31:22.290
I've informed you. That is all.

464
00:32:03.060 --> 00:32:05.060
What on earth do you think you're doing?

465
00:32:07.630 --> 00:32:08.940
What is all this?

466
00:32:13.140 --> 00:32:14.140
Cut it out!

467
00:32:14.610 --> 00:32:16.410
You think I'm going to fall
for this nonsense again?

468
00:32:18.440 --> 00:32:22.280
That's exactly why we use
contracts. Because of people like you.

469
00:32:22.450 --> 00:32:23.580
I know. right?

470
00:32:24.280 --> 00:32:26.120
The way he's just flat-out denying it.

471
00:32:26.550 --> 00:32:28.320
If we hadn't been sending
him that monthly fee.

472
00:32:28.890 --> 00:32:31.260
we would've been totally fooled.

473
00:32:31.320 --> 00:32:32.630
(CEO Cha Byeong Jin)

474
00:32:32.890 --> 00:32:34.060
Don't you remember?

475
00:32:34.690 --> 00:32:37.760
You took the 800 dollars
we sent you every month.

476
00:32:38.230 --> 00:32:40.930
- But you said that was cashback...
- Sir!

477
00:32:42.170 --> 00:32:45.570
That luxury car. with
the title you signed over.

478
00:32:45.910 --> 00:32:48.240
got into a fender bender.

479
00:32:48.510 --> 00:32:52.110
Luckily. we got it fixed at a shop we know.

480
00:32:52.680 --> 00:32:55.820
so we managed to keep the
cost down to 40.000 dollars.

481
00:32:59.720 --> 00:33:02.660
(Article 3. Duty to Cooperate
Regarding Title Provision)

482
00:33:05.630 --> 00:33:08.900
And this seal impression is
from your official seal. correct?

483
00:33:12.930 --> 00:33:15.130
When did you ever show me this?

484
00:33:16.400 --> 00:33:18.400
When did you ever show me this?

485
00:33:19.070 --> 00:33:22.880
You only showed me the very last page!

486
00:33:23.680 --> 00:33:26.280
If you claim you just saw the end.

487
00:33:26.350 --> 00:33:28.950
then next time. you should
initial every page of the contract.

488
00:33:29.480 --> 00:33:30.820
Then maybe someone
will actually believe you.

489
00:33:39.790 --> 00:33:41.960
It was all of you.

490
00:33:44.360 --> 00:33:45.430
All right.

491
00:33:46.070 --> 00:33:48.430
What are you going to do about
the 40.000 dollars for repairs?

492
00:33:49.040 --> 00:33:51.800
Will you be paying in cash? Or card?

493
00:33:54.540 --> 00:33:56.380
You even hung up a fake license.

494
00:33:58.710 --> 00:34:00.150
You darn con artists!

495
00:34:03.350 --> 00:34:04.350
Fake?

496
00:34:05.120 --> 00:34:07.289
- It's not fake.
- Darn it!

497
00:34:07.290 --> 00:34:09.690
Hey. that's crossing the line.

498
00:34:13.360 --> 00:34:14.390
Everything...

499
00:34:14.990 --> 00:34:17.830
was all a part of your scheme!

500
00:34:19.230 --> 00:34:24.170
- Everything!
- Gosh. after we explained it all.

501
00:34:24.900 --> 00:34:26.240
this is just too much!

502
00:34:26.970 --> 00:34:27.970
So unreasonable.

503
00:34:49.960 --> 00:34:51.160
Enough. Take him.

504
00:35:02.840 --> 00:35:04.180
Have you been to any government offices?

505
00:35:06.150 --> 00:35:07.710
What did they say at the police station?

506
00:35:11.050 --> 00:35:13.450
Did anyone. anywhere. take your side?

507
00:35:28.430 --> 00:35:31.000
Let's say I orchestrated
all this. like you claim.

508
00:35:31.940 --> 00:35:32.940
Then...

509
00:35:35.410 --> 00:35:36.680
what else can you possibly do?

510
00:35:40.410 --> 00:35:42.620
Everything was done by the book.

511
00:35:57.560 --> 00:36:00.200
The fact that no one took your side...

512
00:36:05.410 --> 00:36:07.470
means you're the one who's in the wrong.

513
00:36:13.310 --> 00:36:14.310
And one more thing.

514
00:36:17.020 --> 00:36:18.480
That license is real.

515
00:36:31.700 --> 00:36:33.030
No matter how hard I think about it.

516
00:36:34.030 --> 00:36:36.470
I just don't know where it all went wrong.

517
00:36:37.970 --> 00:36:41.440
I have no idea what I did wrong.

518
00:36:42.940 --> 00:36:44.280
I just have no idea.

519
00:36:48.580 --> 00:36:49.680
Driver Oh...

520
00:36:50.420 --> 00:36:53.290
walked into a trap they
set from the very beginning.

521
00:36:53.890 --> 00:36:55.560
No matter how hard he tried to get out.

522
00:36:55.820 --> 00:36:57.360
he couldn't see a way.

523
00:36:58.590 --> 00:37:00.530
He must've been going
through nightmare all by himself.

524
00:37:01.960 --> 00:37:03.400
What do we do about those jerks?

525
00:37:04.800 --> 00:37:06.700
They did everything by the book.

526
00:37:08.070 --> 00:37:09.640
so we'll do the same.

527
00:37:22.780 --> 00:37:26.620
("DUI Fatal Hit-and-Run Driver
Turns Out to Be a Practising Lawyer")

528
00:37:40.430 --> 00:37:42.700
(Game: Taxi Driver)

529
00:37:47.170 --> 00:37:49.480
(88. Taxi Driver)

530
00:37:52.140 --> 00:37:53.150
Hello.

531
00:37:53.380 --> 00:37:57.380
First. thank you for choosing
Rainbow Deluxe Taxi.

532
00:37:57.520 --> 00:38:02.390
For your safety and convenience.
I'll go over a few disclaimers.

533
00:38:02.460 --> 00:38:06.990
The meter will be running
for the duration of the service.

534
00:38:07.160 --> 00:38:11.160
The fare will be calculated and
paid after the service is complete.

535
00:38:11.260 --> 00:38:14.070
and additional surcharges may
apply depending on the circumstances.

536
00:38:14.400 --> 00:38:17.240
After using the taxi.

537
00:38:17.300 --> 00:38:21.510
you must not mention anything
about Rainbow Taxi to anyone else.

538
00:38:21.670 --> 00:38:22.780
We must insist.

539
00:38:23.280 --> 00:38:26.580
Now. if you wish to hire the Deluxe Taxi.

540
00:38:26.950 --> 00:38:28.950
press the blue button on
the left side of the screen.

541
00:38:29.280 --> 00:38:34.220
If not. please press the
red button on the right.

542
00:38:34.290 --> 00:38:36.060
Now. please make your choice.

543
00:38:43.800 --> 00:38:47.530
Under the Passenger Transport Act.
your taxi license has been revoked.

544
00:38:54.210 --> 00:38:55.210
I'm off!

545
00:38:56.510 --> 00:38:58.680
But if you drive without a license
plate even if you're in a rush.

546
00:38:59.180 --> 00:39:00.510
you can be fined.

547
00:39:00.780 --> 00:39:02.450
Please just help me this one time. Please?

548
00:39:02.980 --> 00:39:05.150
The fact that no one took your side...

549
00:39:05.850 --> 00:39:08.290
means you're the one who's in the wrong.

550
00:39:28.610 --> 00:39:30.710
(24MA 5283)

551
00:39:38.480 --> 00:39:39.650
(Deluxe Taxi)

552
00:39:48.090 --> 00:39:49.800
You look way better in the photo.

553
00:39:49.960 --> 00:39:53.700
- What? I look way better in person.
- What are you doing? Let's go.

554
00:39:53.770 --> 00:39:55.970
- Are we leaving? Let's go!
- Let's go.

555
00:40:03.940 --> 00:40:04.940
(24MA 5283)

556
00:40:10.850 --> 00:40:13.220
Noblesse Motors.

557
00:40:16.160 --> 00:40:17.760
(The Champion of the Used
Car Market. Why? It's "Noblesse"!)

558
00:40:17.820 --> 00:40:21.730
They handle all auto brokering.
Used car sales are their main thing.

559
00:40:21.990 --> 00:40:23.360
What's their capital structure like?

560
00:40:23.700 --> 00:40:27.000
The dealership building is fully mortgaged.

561
00:40:27.200 --> 00:40:30.270
and their cars are tied up in
financing from a capital firm.

562
00:40:30.500 --> 00:40:33.770
So they're running a huge dealership
with none of their own money.

563
00:40:34.270 --> 00:40:37.080
If things go south. they
don't stand to lose a thing.

564
00:40:37.340 --> 00:40:38.910
Smart guy.

565
00:40:39.280 --> 00:40:41.580
Too bad he doesn't use
that brain for something good.

566
00:40:41.910 --> 00:40:43.150
You're heading to the
dealership first. right?

567
00:40:43.680 --> 00:40:44.680
That's the plan.

568
00:40:45.020 --> 00:40:48.720
Then I'll look for the foreign car
registered in Driver Oh's name.

569
00:40:49.090 --> 00:40:50.090
Okay.

570
00:40:50.760 --> 00:40:55.530
Noblesse Motors.

571
00:40:56.200 --> 00:40:57.200
Noblesse?

572
00:41:00.370 --> 00:41:01.370
Noblesse.

573
00:41:02.300 --> 00:41:03.300
What?

574
00:41:03.770 --> 00:41:06.610
Nothing. Let's just go. for now.

575
00:41:19.790 --> 00:41:24.520
(Noblesse)

576
00:41:24.690 --> 00:41:27.730
(Deluxe Taxi)

577
00:41:28.160 --> 00:41:32.260
You know. that "Noblesse"
sign looks really familiar.

578
00:41:32.770 --> 00:41:34.130
Now that you mention it.

579
00:41:34.770 --> 00:41:39.070
it does feel strangely familiar to me too.

580
00:41:39.240 --> 00:41:41.670
It's almost nostalgic. isn't it?

581
00:41:41.970 --> 00:41:42.980
Yes. same here.

582
00:41:43.540 --> 00:41:44.980
And here I thought you
two remembered something.

583
00:41:49.250 --> 00:41:50.780
(Noblesse Private Taxi
and Delivery Service)

584
00:41:51.450 --> 00:41:52.450
What?

585
00:41:58.990 --> 00:42:01.230
I'll be right back after
one last test drive.

586
00:42:01.590 --> 00:42:03.460
- Wait!
- What's wrong?

587
00:42:03.700 --> 00:42:05.030
Come on. What is it?

588
00:42:05.300 --> 00:42:07.169
I got you now. you jerk.

589
00:42:07.170 --> 00:42:09.000
Hey. where are you off to all of a sudden?

590
00:42:09.670 --> 00:42:10.670
I was wondering the same thing.

591
00:42:11.870 --> 00:42:12.870
Chief Choi!

592
00:42:20.150 --> 00:42:21.750
What? What is it? What's going on?

593
00:42:21.810 --> 00:42:23.350
It's the car thief! The
one who stole our car!

594
00:42:23.650 --> 00:42:26.650
- Wait!
- Oh. no. What now. Driver Kim?

595
00:42:27.250 --> 00:42:28.320
I'm not sure.

596
00:42:28.590 --> 00:42:29.590
What should we do?

597
00:42:30.290 --> 00:42:31.290
Hey. you!

598
00:42:34.860 --> 00:42:35.900
Here to look at a car?

599
00:42:36.500 --> 00:42:37.500
You don't recognise me?

600
00:42:38.660 --> 00:42:40.270
I'm not sure. Who are you?

601
00:42:42.540 --> 00:42:43.540
Then what about this car?

602
00:42:43.770 --> 00:42:45.240
(72S 5493)

603
00:42:45.340 --> 00:42:46.470
Still don't recognise me?

604
00:42:59.690 --> 00:43:01.390
You're the one who sold your "memories."

605
00:43:01.650 --> 00:43:03.720
You said you were just
taking it for a test spin.

606
00:43:04.460 --> 00:43:05.720
and then you just took off.

607
00:43:07.290 --> 00:43:08.290
Pay me the rest.

608
00:43:09.300 --> 00:43:10.730
Either that. or give me the car!

609
00:43:11.660 --> 00:43:14.530
- What money?
- Listen to this guy.

610
00:43:14.970 --> 00:43:16.140
So you're going to play dumb?

611
00:43:16.270 --> 00:43:20.540
I acquired the car per the
contract. Why would I play dumb?

612
00:43:20.670 --> 00:43:22.540
What? According to the contract?

613
00:43:22.680 --> 00:43:26.510
It broke down during the test
drive. Turns out the engine was shot.

614
00:43:26.680 --> 00:43:27.949
The repair estimate was 10.000 dollars.

615
00:43:27.950 --> 00:43:29.980
so I deducted that per the contract.

616
00:43:30.050 --> 00:43:32.550
- That's a lie!
- Do you have any proof?

617
00:43:33.050 --> 00:43:35.250
I'm the proof. you jerk.
I inspected it myself!

618
00:43:35.320 --> 00:43:38.220
What is your problem?
Seriously. give it a rest.

619
00:43:38.590 --> 00:43:39.660
What's all this commotion?

620
00:43:40.860 --> 00:43:43.360
He just showed up out of nowhere
and is making a scene over money.

621
00:43:43.430 --> 00:43:46.300
Look who's talking! You've
got some nerve blaming me.

622
00:43:46.670 --> 00:43:48.930
Choi! Get this guy out of here.

623
00:43:49.270 --> 00:43:50.470
What do you mean. Choi... Hey...

624
00:43:51.440 --> 00:43:53.770
What? Gosh.

625
00:43:54.270 --> 00:43:56.510
Hey! Let go!

626
00:43:56.680 --> 00:43:59.710
Hey. you! Is your last name Choi?
Which Choi clan are you from?

627
00:43:59.780 --> 00:44:02.350
- I'm a Choi too!
- What's going on?

628
00:44:04.780 --> 00:44:06.850
Gosh! Oh. dear.

629
00:44:17.530 --> 00:44:18.830
You went in there ready
to tear the place down.

630
00:44:19.970 --> 00:44:22.640
I almost got into some
real trouble. Gosh. my back.

631
00:44:23.540 --> 00:44:25.970
Gosh. I've never met a
Choi who was that violent.

632
00:44:26.370 --> 00:44:27.970
He's like one of the Choi
clan of the Silla Dynasty.

633
00:44:47.060 --> 00:44:49.460
I found where the luxury
car registered to Driver Oh is.

634
00:44:50.830 --> 00:44:53.130
- Where is it?
- It's not far from here.

635
00:44:53.670 --> 00:44:54.830
Should we head there first?

636
00:44:55.300 --> 00:44:57.700
Wait. this car hit someone.

637
00:45:06.650 --> 00:45:07.650
Goodness.

638
00:45:08.480 --> 00:45:10.950
Do you know how much it costs
to rent a luxury car for a month?

639
00:45:11.720 --> 00:45:15.550
- Three grand.
- It's a luxury car. Four grand.

640
00:45:15.790 --> 00:45:17.620
It's 15.000 dollars.

641
00:45:18.320 --> 00:45:22.490
- How much? It's 15.000 dollars?
- If that's for a legitimate rental.

642
00:45:23.060 --> 00:45:25.400
then they must be charging
much more for that luxury car.

643
00:45:26.230 --> 00:45:29.200
- Why?
- If it's in Driver Oh's name.

644
00:45:29.800 --> 00:45:33.210
then it's pretty obvious
what kind of clients they have.

645
00:45:33.540 --> 00:45:34.540
And what kind is that?

646
00:45:35.010 --> 00:45:37.180
People who can't rent a
car under their own name.

647
00:45:37.980 --> 00:45:41.710
Either they're already criminals.
or they're about to become one.

648
00:45:42.480 --> 00:45:43.480
It's one or the other.

649
00:45:43.620 --> 00:45:46.490
Shouldn't we get Driver Oh out
of that contract before it's late?

650
00:45:46.690 --> 00:45:48.450
Let's go. gorgeous.

651
00:45:54.260 --> 00:45:55.960
First things first. We
need to get that car back.

652
00:45:58.030 --> 00:45:59.230
(Car-Free Street: 10am to 6pm)

653
00:45:59.930 --> 00:46:01.300
So many cars!

654
00:46:03.900 --> 00:46:08.440
- Where to? Straight ahead?
- Yes! Let's roll!

655
00:46:09.780 --> 00:46:13.710
Ring. ring. Coming through.

656
00:46:13.780 --> 00:46:16.850
Hey. don't chicken out.
We didn't hit them. Floor it!

657
00:46:16.920 --> 00:46:17.920
Get out of the way!

658
00:46:18.220 --> 00:46:22.790
Ring. ring. Got some nerve?

659
00:46:23.190 --> 00:46:27.590
- Watch out for that guy up ahead.
- What on earth?

660
00:46:27.660 --> 00:46:28.660
Ring!

661
00:46:30.060 --> 00:46:31.060
What was that?

662
00:46:31.400 --> 00:46:33.469
- That jerk. Why isn't he moving?
- What?

663
00:46:33.470 --> 00:46:34.530
Let's go!

664
00:46:36.200 --> 00:46:38.240
Are you okay? Should we get out of the way?

665
00:46:38.300 --> 00:46:40.740
They'll go around us. Those jerks.

666
00:46:44.780 --> 00:46:46.410
- Oh. no.
- Are you okay?

667
00:46:49.380 --> 00:46:52.080
How could you hit him for
real? Just chill. I'll handle this.

668
00:46:52.220 --> 00:46:53.220
Hey. you crazy jerk!

669
00:46:53.290 --> 00:46:56.290
My neck. It's completely shattered.

670
00:46:56.360 --> 00:46:58.020
Gosh. what are we going to do about this?

671
00:47:00.430 --> 00:47:01.790
You scratched my car.

672
00:47:02.490 --> 00:47:04.230
You rich. kid?

673
00:47:04.600 --> 00:47:06.630
This paint job alone costs 10.000 dollars.

674
00:47:07.630 --> 00:47:10.040
- Let's just go.
- I asked if you're rich. you punk!

675
00:47:14.070 --> 00:47:15.070
I'm sorry.

676
00:47:15.670 --> 00:47:16.880
What are you looking at. jerks?

677
00:47:17.280 --> 00:47:19.240
- Goodness.
- Go away!

678
00:47:19.750 --> 00:47:21.110
All right!

679
00:47:22.380 --> 00:47:23.380
They're insane!

680
00:47:31.590 --> 00:47:34.630
That's right. We've got to obey the light.

681
00:47:35.960 --> 00:47:38.900
Gosh. darn. This place is a madhouse.

682
00:47:39.260 --> 00:47:42.970
Hey. old lady! What. are you deaf?

683
00:47:43.540 --> 00:47:45.440
I said move to the side!

684
00:47:45.740 --> 00:47:50.010
- Dude. she can't hear you.
- Hey. lady! Pick up the pace!

685
00:47:50.310 --> 00:47:51.310
Here's a gift!

686
00:47:51.980 --> 00:47:53.310
Are you kidding me right now?

687
00:47:53.950 --> 00:47:55.410
Drive safe.

688
00:47:58.920 --> 00:48:01.090
- Darn it!
- Hey! What was that?

689
00:48:01.590 --> 00:48:03.560
Hold on. Hey. you!

690
00:48:03.620 --> 00:48:05.420
Hold up. Just a moment.
You. there. Hold it.

691
00:48:05.490 --> 00:48:08.560
- What are you doing?
- Hey. cabbie. move your car.

692
00:48:09.360 --> 00:48:10.760
Move your car. cabbie.

693
00:48:13.170 --> 00:48:14.670
You think you can just park here?

694
00:48:15.630 --> 00:48:16.700
You must be a real busy guy.

695
00:48:17.340 --> 00:48:18.340
Right?

696
00:48:18.800 --> 00:48:22.140
Hey. you dropped this.
Is it yours? Now. you jerk.

697
00:48:25.210 --> 00:48:27.550
This is fun! Yes. real fun.

698
00:48:27.880 --> 00:48:30.550
All right. Time for Gear Second.

699
00:48:30.650 --> 00:48:32.420
Let's see you block this. you jerk.

700
00:48:33.220 --> 00:48:34.220
You jerk!

701
00:48:38.390 --> 00:48:40.890
This is a blast! This is so much fun.

702
00:48:41.260 --> 00:48:43.400
Where are you going?

703
00:48:43.460 --> 00:48:46.570
- Trying to run? Give it a shot.
- Hey. what on earth?

704
00:48:47.330 --> 00:48:48.930
What in the world is this?

705
00:48:54.670 --> 00:48:55.670
Darn it.

706
00:48:57.380 --> 00:48:59.080
Got you. you little jerks.

707
00:48:59.410 --> 00:49:01.450
(Dings and Dongs Auto Restoration)

708
00:49:03.380 --> 00:49:04.780
Get out of here. you jerk!

709
00:49:06.150 --> 00:49:08.190
Darn. he thinks he's hot stuff.

710
00:49:09.390 --> 00:49:12.520
He doesn't know who he's up against.

711
00:49:22.170 --> 00:49:25.940
So these aren't just for show.
You actually plan on killing them.

712
00:49:26.140 --> 00:49:27.340
What. you think we came to save you?

713
00:49:27.910 --> 00:49:29.440
It's too late to run. you jerk.

714
00:49:33.850 --> 00:49:36.110
- I was thinking the same thing.
- Then die. you jerk!

715
00:49:49.800 --> 00:49:51.660
He's really going for the calf kicks.

716
00:49:52.560 --> 00:49:53.670
Stay back.

717
00:49:53.700 --> 00:49:54.730
Stay back. you jerk!

718
00:50:07.280 --> 00:50:08.280
Good grief.

719
00:50:14.420 --> 00:50:16.190
Let's go clean this up.

720
00:50:23.100 --> 00:50:24.830
(Vehicle Registration. Auto
Lease. Used Car Financial Lease)

721
00:50:24.900 --> 00:50:26.730
(Client: Oh Man Soo)

722
00:50:26.800 --> 00:50:27.800
(Void without QR Code. Contract number)

723
00:50:30.640 --> 00:50:32.540
(Acquisition cost: 617.000 dollars)

724
00:50:40.210 --> 00:50:41.810
Good. It doesn't seem to
have any other damage.

725
00:50:41.910 --> 00:50:43.580
Let's take it back and
cancel the lease. then.

726
00:50:44.320 --> 00:50:46.150
Okay. got it.

727
00:50:47.290 --> 00:50:48.490
Apparently. we can't
terminate the contract.

728
00:50:49.090 --> 00:50:50.090
What?

729
00:50:50.590 --> 00:50:53.490
So. the car is currently
leased under Driver Oh's name.

730
00:50:53.560 --> 00:50:56.130
- they won't let us cancel early.
- What if we can't cancel?

731
00:50:56.160 --> 00:50:58.130
We either have to transfer
the lease to someone else.

732
00:50:58.200 --> 00:51:00.570
or we're stuck with it
until the lease is up.

733
00:51:00.930 --> 00:51:02.270
Are there any other options?

734
00:51:02.830 --> 00:51:03.840
No.

735
00:51:04.470 --> 00:51:07.870
What? So we got the car back.
but we still have to pay for it?

736
00:51:10.080 --> 00:51:13.150
Then we'll just have to get
more money out of those guys.

737
00:51:15.080 --> 00:51:16.180
Go Eun.

738
00:51:16.720 --> 00:51:18.220
I need you to pick out a car for me.

739
00:51:18.680 --> 00:51:19.690
A car?

740
00:51:20.620 --> 00:51:24.360
We got Driver Oh's car back.
so now I'll buy a car we need.

741
00:51:24.590 --> 00:51:25.720
You're buying a car?

742
00:51:26.120 --> 00:51:29.860
- From Noblesse?
- Right. If Go Eun picks one for me.

743
00:51:30.600 --> 00:51:31.830
I'll go buy it.

744
00:51:33.500 --> 00:51:37.240
Okay. I'll find something perfect for you.

745
00:51:40.810 --> 00:51:42.210
(Private Taxis. Delivery
Trucks. Commercial Vehicles)

746
00:51:42.270 --> 00:51:43.610
(False Listing Compensation Program)

747
00:51:48.610 --> 00:51:49.650
Hello.

748
00:51:50.080 --> 00:51:51.350
Hello.

749
00:51:51.750 --> 00:51:54.090
Is there a particular model...

750
00:51:55.150 --> 00:51:57.759
- you're looking for?
- This is my first car.

751
00:51:57.760 --> 00:52:00.260
so I'm not sure what to look for.

752
00:52:01.230 --> 00:52:04.400
I'm just looking for something
that's as sturdy and safe as can be.

753
00:52:06.430 --> 00:52:07.430
Are you working?

754
00:52:08.730 --> 00:52:11.840
Yes. I just started at a small factory.

755
00:52:12.240 --> 00:52:13.470
Congratulations.

756
00:52:14.910 --> 00:52:16.839
- Are you married?
- Yes.

757
00:52:16.840 --> 00:52:20.180
- Any kids?
- My wife is seven months pregnant.

758
00:52:20.250 --> 00:52:21.250
Hallelujah!

759
00:52:21.880 --> 00:52:24.879
A double blessing! Double congratulations!

760
00:52:24.880 --> 00:52:25.980
- My goodness.
- Thank you.

761
00:52:28.420 --> 00:52:33.130
Because of the baby. I was
determined to get a loan...

762
00:52:33.490 --> 00:52:34.989
- to buy a brand-new car.
- You came to the right place.

763
00:52:34.990 --> 00:52:38.230
Used cars are practically new now.

764
00:52:38.260 --> 00:52:41.000
Take a look. Let's see here.

765
00:52:42.730 --> 00:52:46.869
Seven months pregnant? We'd
better get you into a car fast.

766
00:52:46.870 --> 00:52:49.140
Yes. for my wife's hospital visits.

767
00:52:49.170 --> 00:52:52.480
Okay. So for commuting. hospital visits.

768
00:52:52.610 --> 00:52:54.710
and family trips later on.

769
00:52:54.850 --> 00:52:57.850
We've got the perfect first
car for all of that right here.

770
00:52:59.020 --> 00:53:01.090
All right. let's go. Not these ones.

771
00:53:01.150 --> 00:53:03.690
- We have a sturdy. safe car there.
- Okay.

772
00:53:03.860 --> 00:53:05.620
We have just one left. A real sturdy one.

773
00:53:09.430 --> 00:53:10.500
(CEO's Office)

774
00:53:10.560 --> 00:53:13.060
What are you talking about? How
could you let them take the car?

775
00:53:13.600 --> 00:53:16.330
To who? What? A taxi driver?

776
00:53:16.400 --> 00:53:18.470
(CEO Cha Byeong Jin)

777
00:53:22.970 --> 00:53:24.010
Hey.

778
00:53:24.640 --> 00:53:27.310
You wanted to drive a car
but were too cheap to pay for it?

779
00:53:30.220 --> 00:53:32.620
Bring the car back right now
while I'm still asking nicely.

780
00:53:33.550 --> 00:53:35.590
Before I have you thrown
in jail for aggravated theft.

781
00:53:39.790 --> 00:53:42.590
Don't drive if you can't afford
one. Bunch of scumbags.

782
00:53:46.030 --> 00:53:47.030
Sir.

783
00:53:47.470 --> 00:53:50.600
Manager Yang says he's hooked a pushover.

784
00:53:56.480 --> 00:53:58.580
- What about the contract?
- He's working on it inside now.

785
00:54:11.720 --> 00:54:13.930
All right. all done.

786
00:54:14.960 --> 00:54:16.899
Thank you so much for
helping me find a great car.

787
00:54:16.900 --> 00:54:18.900
Not at all. The pleasure is all mine.

788
00:54:19.760 --> 00:54:22.300
I'll transfer the down
payment by the end of the day.

789
00:54:24.040 --> 00:54:26.470
By the way. about the residual value...

790
00:54:26.510 --> 00:54:29.440
The 20.000 dollars. will
you be paying that in cash?

791
00:54:30.780 --> 00:54:33.140
I'm sorry? Residual value?

792
00:54:35.010 --> 00:54:37.150
You don't know what residual value is?

793
00:54:38.480 --> 00:54:40.090
What are you talking about?

794
00:54:41.290 --> 00:54:43.490
There was nothing
about that in the contract.

795
00:54:44.690 --> 00:54:48.060
Gosh. Looks like I missed a page. Darn it.

796
00:54:49.490 --> 00:54:50.500
Ta-da!

797
00:54:51.530 --> 00:54:54.470
See? It says "separate payment" right here.

798
00:54:55.900 --> 00:54:58.340
Who does business like this?

799
00:55:00.070 --> 00:55:01.340
What do you take me for?

800
00:55:04.810 --> 00:55:06.010
I'm not buying this car.

801
00:55:06.340 --> 00:55:07.410
Hey. you jerk!

802
00:55:09.580 --> 00:55:13.220
I wasted all this time
nicely explaining everything.

803
00:55:14.220 --> 00:55:15.420
and now you're backing out?

804
00:55:17.760 --> 00:55:18.960
Fine. don't buy it.

805
00:55:20.830 --> 00:55:22.130
How much was it again?

806
00:55:23.130 --> 00:55:26.770
Fine. Just pay the cancellation
penalty of 20.000 dollars.

807
00:55:26.970 --> 00:55:27.970
What?

808
00:55:29.300 --> 00:55:33.070
You're a complete con
artist. I'm not buying it.

809
00:55:33.810 --> 00:55:37.180
That's enough. You
went too far. A con artist?

810
00:55:39.040 --> 00:55:40.180
What are you talking about?

811
00:55:41.080 --> 00:55:42.350
What do you take me for?

812
00:55:43.480 --> 00:55:44.680
I'm not a con artist.

813
00:56:08.070 --> 00:56:10.380
Perfect timing. You're
the boss here. right?

814
00:56:10.940 --> 00:56:14.350
That fake law degree on the
wall? If this isn't a scam. what is?

815
00:56:14.410 --> 00:56:17.850
It's not fake. The certificate's real.

816
00:56:18.680 --> 00:56:21.820
Hey. You're in big trouble now.

817
00:56:24.690 --> 00:56:27.490
I'm reporting all of you to the police.

818
00:56:51.950 --> 00:56:53.690
For false accusations and defamation.

819
00:56:54.450 --> 00:56:56.120
That's a pretty serious offence.

820
00:57:00.930 --> 00:57:02.730
My employee explained everything.

821
00:57:03.160 --> 00:57:05.160
and if you had any questions.
you should've asked.

822
00:57:06.360 --> 00:57:07.800
And you're going to call the cops on us?

823
00:57:10.170 --> 00:57:11.340
Manager Go. come here.

824
00:57:17.880 --> 00:57:18.980
Stand up straight.

825
00:57:23.650 --> 00:57:24.750
Clench your teeth.

826
00:57:28.290 --> 00:57:29.990
There. That should do it.

827
00:57:31.390 --> 00:57:34.260
Manager Go. get a medical
report and go file a report.

828
00:57:34.330 --> 00:57:36.630
- Manager Yang. be his witness.
- Yes. sir.

829
00:57:36.700 --> 00:57:39.060
He'll face a fine of a few
thousand for mutual assault.

830
00:57:39.400 --> 00:57:40.670
Understood. boss.

831
00:57:41.370 --> 00:57:42.370
Darn it.

832
00:57:45.870 --> 00:57:46.970
But here's the thing.

833
00:57:47.670 --> 00:57:51.080
Manager Go makes a lot
more money than you do.

834
00:57:52.410 --> 00:57:54.080
So the compensation you'll
owe for his lost wages...

835
00:57:54.350 --> 00:57:55.780
will probably be as much as the car itself.

836
00:57:56.610 --> 00:57:58.080
When did I ever hit him?

837
00:58:00.250 --> 00:58:01.620
You're the one who hit him!

838
00:58:21.640 --> 00:58:26.240
I see you're happily married.
and you have a kid on the way.

839
00:58:28.510 --> 00:58:29.980
And I was just looking
at your home address...

840
00:58:31.180 --> 00:58:32.480
It's a nice neighbourhood.

841
00:58:32.750 --> 00:58:34.390
but I hear there are many
accidents around there.

842
00:58:44.000 --> 00:58:45.930
I'd be worried about your
wife and your unborn child.

843
00:58:49.470 --> 00:58:51.670
Please. spare me.

844
00:58:52.400 --> 00:58:55.810
I'm begging you. please spare me.

845
00:58:57.540 --> 00:58:58.580
What are you talking about?

846
00:58:59.240 --> 00:59:00.650
I just sell cars.

847
00:59:09.850 --> 00:59:11.220
Please. spare me.

848
00:59:12.920 --> 00:59:14.130
Please. spare me.

849
00:59:16.330 --> 00:59:17.330
And...

850
00:59:23.270 --> 00:59:25.300
(Bar Exam Certificate of
Qualification. Cha Byeong Jin)

851
00:59:26.200 --> 00:59:27.810
That's real. by the way.

852
00:59:33.710 --> 00:59:34.810
You jerk.

853
00:59:37.620 --> 00:59:39.620
(Deluxe Taxi)

854
00:59:54.570 --> 00:59:57.500
Is he okay? This is just heartbreaking.

855
00:59:58.000 --> 01:00:01.240
- You can't leave without your gift.
- A gift?

856
01:00:01.610 --> 01:00:04.080
A gift for your unborn child.

857
01:00:05.840 --> 01:00:08.350
Go on. take it. Say
"thank you" and take it.

858
01:00:09.950 --> 01:00:12.380
How cute. Your ride's here.

859
01:00:12.720 --> 01:00:16.860
- Snap out of it. You have to drive.
- Sir.

860
01:00:17.720 --> 01:00:19.090
Here are your car keys.

861
01:00:21.290 --> 01:00:23.160
Take them.

862
01:00:24.060 --> 01:00:26.400
- Take them.
- Take them. you jerk.

863
01:00:30.070 --> 01:00:32.070
I said take them. you jerk.

864
01:00:46.020 --> 01:00:47.020
What?

865
01:00:48.150 --> 01:00:50.660
- Stop.
- Hey! Stop!

866
01:00:50.720 --> 01:00:51.720
You hit it. didn't you?

867
01:00:55.460 --> 01:00:56.530
Are you crazy?

868
01:00:57.860 --> 01:00:58.860
What do we do?

869
01:01:13.610 --> 01:01:15.150
Is everyone okay?

870
01:01:17.680 --> 01:01:19.880
Is anyone hurt?

871
01:01:23.150 --> 01:01:26.060
I thought I heard someone yell "hit it."

872
01:01:26.220 --> 01:01:28.660
so I hit it without even thinking.

873
01:01:31.330 --> 01:01:34.370
- Wait. is this car scratched?
- Hey. no! Easy does it.

874
01:01:36.400 --> 01:01:38.870
- It's hot!
- Oh. dear. what are we going to do?

875
01:01:39.240 --> 01:01:40.570
- Out of the way.
- Oh. dear.

876
01:01:40.610 --> 01:01:42.040
- Get out of the way!
- Oh. no. what are we going to do?

877
01:01:42.940 --> 01:01:45.910
You idiot. move! I
said. get out of the way!

878
01:01:48.750 --> 01:01:49.910
You're the buyer. right?

879
01:01:50.680 --> 01:01:51.850
What have I done?

880
01:01:52.120 --> 01:01:55.150
It looks like I've
completely ruined your deal.

881
01:01:55.420 --> 01:01:58.660
The deal is officially void.

882
01:01:59.390 --> 01:02:00.390
Void.

883
01:02:04.660 --> 01:02:05.700
You're right.

884
01:02:06.630 --> 01:02:08.130
I'm not signing the contract.

885
01:02:10.070 --> 01:02:11.170
Thank you.

886
01:02:12.070 --> 01:02:15.870
- Thank you.
- No. wait!

887
01:02:15.940 --> 01:02:17.080
Move.

888
01:02:17.780 --> 01:02:20.880
- Get out of the way!
- I'm not an irresponsible person.

889
01:02:20.950 --> 01:02:24.780
- I get it. now just move. darn it!
- No. I'll take full responsibility.

890
01:02:24.850 --> 01:02:26.680
- That's enough.
- What?

891
01:02:28.590 --> 01:02:29.590
Yes. sir.

892
01:02:33.390 --> 01:02:35.690
Thanks to you. a perfectly
good deal is ruined.

893
01:02:37.160 --> 01:02:39.400
- Yes.
- And our display model's scratched.

894
01:02:40.370 --> 01:02:41.430
So how are you going to make this right?

895
01:02:44.670 --> 01:02:45.840
In that case.

896
01:02:48.370 --> 01:02:49.540
I'll buy it.

897
01:02:51.440 --> 01:02:54.180
I'll also pay for the
repairs on that other car.

898
01:02:59.280 --> 01:03:01.050
It's only right.

899
01:03:06.620 --> 01:03:07.630
Perfect.

900
01:03:12.960 --> 01:03:14.800
Somebody show our customer inside.

901
01:03:15.270 --> 01:03:16.270
Yes. sir.

902
01:03:20.300 --> 01:03:23.210
I'm Go Deok Su. your
dealer. It's a pleasure.

903
01:03:23.270 --> 01:03:24.740
Yes. I'm looking forward to it.

904
01:03:26.310 --> 01:03:27.650
That's some outfit.

905
01:03:28.150 --> 01:03:29.310
It's quite something.

906
01:03:29.580 --> 01:03:32.250
It's from the new collection.

907
01:03:33.450 --> 01:03:35.750
By the way. how much is that car?

908
01:03:37.190 --> 01:03:40.890
Driver Kim Do Gi. how's
the used car you just bought?

909
01:03:41.890 --> 01:03:43.630
I think I might've overpaid.

910
01:04:13.390 --> 01:04:14.490
Driver Kim Do Gi.

911
01:04:15.660 --> 01:04:18.230
I think I paid for this car
more than I was expecting to.

912
01:04:32.280 --> 01:04:34.480
Driver Kim. is something wrong?

913
01:04:50.090 --> 01:04:51.100
(Safety first)

914
01:05:09.010 --> 01:05:12.050
Driver Kim Do Gi. Can you hear me?

915
01:05:13.050 --> 01:05:14.090
Driver Kim?

916
01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:34.810
(Special thanks to Yoon Si
Yoon for his guest appearance.)

917
01:05:53.020 --> 01:05:56.030
(Taxi Driver 3)

918
01:05:57.800 --> 01:06:00.330
{\an8}You want to go home. don't
you? Then do a job for me.

919
01:06:00.400 --> 01:06:03.800
{\an8}I'm here to buy cars. I
need 100 on my carrier. fast.

920
01:06:03.870 --> 01:06:06.070
{\an8}That jerk is driving a Car
Carrier. buying up used cars.

921
01:06:06.170 --> 01:06:07.970
{\an8}So what's their take on me?

922
01:06:08.440 --> 01:06:11.480
{\an8}I can't figure out what this guy is up to.

923
01:06:12.840 --> 01:06:15.010
{\an8}Was this his plan all along? To scam me?

924
01:06:16.180 --> 01:06:17.550
{\an8}Hey! Get everyone together. Now.

925
01:06:18.420 --> 01:06:20.220
{\an8}You messed with the wrong guy.

926
01:06:21.490 --> 01:06:23.620
{\an8}- Choi.
- We're Team Kim.

927
01:06:23.720 --> 01:06:24.790
{\an8}Hey. Kim.

927
01:06:25.305 --> 01:07:25.231
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today
